# Datamodel.ai — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router — Server Components and Server Actions only
- PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM — JSONB for CDM/UDM data
- Clerk — org-aware multi-tenant auth
- Inngest — all background jobs
- Claude API via Vercel AI SDK — generateObject + Zod only
- shadcn/ui + Tailwind

## Non-negotiable rules

1. Server Actions for ALL mutations — never use API routes for mutations
2. generateObject + Zod for ALL AI structured output — never parse raw text
3. Inngest for ALL background jobs — never block API routes with sync
4. org_id on EVERY DB query — never query without tenant scope
5. Drizzle `with:` for relations — no N+1 queries
6. revalidatePath after EVERY mutation
7. One migration per story — never bundle schema changes
8. Verification script per story — scripts/verify-s{N}.{N}.ts
9. status = 'production' filter at DB layer — not in application code
10. No hardcoded secrets — process.env only
11. Exponential backoff on all connector API calls
12. All sync operations logged to sync_logs

## Auth pattern (every server action)
const { orgId, userId } = await auth();
if (!orgId || !userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

## DB query pattern (every query)
await db.query.tableName.findMany({
  where: and(eq(table.orgId, orgId), ...otherConditions),
});

## AI pattern
import { generateObject } from 'ai';
import { z } from 'zod';
const { object } = await generateObject({
  model: anthropic(DEFAULT_MODEL),
  schema: MyZodSchema,
  prompt: '...',
});

## File structure
- lib/actions/ — one file per domain (e.g. fields.ts, sources.ts)
- lib/db/schema/ — one file per entity group
- lib/connectors/ — one folder per source
- lib/inngest/functions/ — one file per job
- scripts/ — verify-s{N}.{N}.ts per story

## What NOT to do
- No client-side data fetching (no useEffect + fetch)
- No direct db instantiation outside lib/db/index.ts
- No AI calls that return raw text and parse with regex
- No sync work in API routes
- No queries without org_id scope
- No hard deletes — status = 'deprecated' always
- No field reaches production without approved_by + approved_at set
- Agents only ever read status = 'production' fields — enforced at DB layer